.TH "hvc_put_chars" 9 "hvc_put_chars" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hvc_put_chars \- send characters to firmware for denoted vterm adapter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hvc_put_chars
.BI "(uint32_t vtermno "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vtermno" 12
The vtermno or unit_address of the adapter from which the data
originated.
.IP "buf" 12
The character buffer that contains the character data to send to
firmware. Must be at least 16 bytes, even if count is less than 16.
.IP "count" 12
Send this number of characters.
